						<summary>

						<p>Kūrattaḷvār shrine, west wall, proper left.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1430, Vibhava, Jyēshṭha śu. Pañchamī, Friday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1508 A.D., May 5, Friday. 41.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record the purchase and grant of land by Śrīraṅgarāja, son of Kuchēṭi Vōbuḷarāju of Kāśyapa-<hi rend="italic">gōtra,</hi> Āpastamba-<hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi> and Yajuś-<hi rend="italic">śakhā,</hi> for offerings to Kūrattāḻvār.</p>						

						</summary>
